Exactly, overrides of interface methods require Java 1.6.
This is the case for many of the existing @Overrides in DataSourceProxy, PoolProperties and ConnectionPool and others, which is one of the reasons jdbc pool won't compile currently with Java 5.

Does this mean that those @Overrides should be removed?

However, AFAICT the patch only adds overrides for methods which override superclass methods, so will compile with Java 1.5.
